Backend CRUD System

This project is a backend application built with .NET following the MVC (Model-View-Controller) architecture. Its main purpose is to handle CRUD (Create, Read, Update, Delete) operations in a structured and scalable way.

Features

Implementation of CRUD operations with .NET

Use of MVC pattern, generating the database directly from the Model

Separation of concerns between models, controllers, and data access

Integration ready to communicate with the frontend application

Purpose

The project was created to serve as a study base for backend development with .NET. By using MVC and database creation from the model, it demonstrates best practices for building maintainable and extendable backend systems.
